@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "Requirements"
Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
You will need the following things to run the program:

- Kickstart 2.0 or newer (I think)

- Files to join

@ENDNODE

@NODE 3. "Installation"
Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~

Hmm, installation ???

Just copy the IntuiJoin program to whereever you want it to be, for example
C:  SYS:Tools  SYS:Utilities  or something like that :)

@ENDNODE

@NODE 4. "Usage"
How to use it
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
It is pretty similar to IntuiSplit.

Press the 'First File' gadget to bring up a requester.
Now you can only choose *.0 files, a file that ends with '.0'.
This is because it's made yo be used with IntuiSplit, or other split
programs which splits up the files in 'filename.partnumber'.

When you have selected a .0-file, just press the 'Join' gadget.
And your full file will have the same name as the .0-file, except .0 ofcourse.

@ENDNODE

